    <title type="html"><![CDATA[R na co dzień]]></title>
    <link href="http://wbzyl.github.com/ppn/blog/2012/02/17/r-na-co-dzien/"/>
    <updated>2012-02-17T17:25:00+01:00</updated>
    <id>http://wbzyl.github.com/ppn/blog/2012/02/17/r-na-co-dzien</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Możemy pracować na konsoli R albo korzystając z trybu <em>ESS</em> w Emacsie.</p>

<p>Polecenia, które wykonujemy codziennie:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><pre><code class='r'>source<span class="p">(</span><span class="s">&quot;hello.r&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>
objects<span class="p">()</span>
ls<span class="p">()</span>

z <span class="o">&lt;-</span> read.table<span class="p">(</span><span class="s">&quot;http://inf.ug.edu.pl/~wbzyl/r/2x2&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>
z
  V1 V2
<span class="m">1</span>  <span class="m">1</span>  <span class="m">2</span>
<span class="m">2</span>  <span class="m">3</span>  <span class="m">4</span>

save<span class="p">(</span>z<span class="p">)</span>

rm<span class="p">(</span>z<span class="p">)</span>
rm<span class="p">(</span>list <span class="o">=</span> ls<span class="p">())</span>

load<span class="p">(</span>z<span class="p">)</span>

methods<span class="p">(</span>ls<span class="p">)</span>
methods<span class="p">(</span>class<span class="o">=</span><span class="s">&quot;default&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>

?ls

x <span class="o">&lt;-</span> c<span class="p">(</span><span class="m">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="m">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="m">3</span><span class="p">)</span>
class<span class="p">(</span>x<span class="p">)</span>
  <span class="p">[</span><span class="m">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="s">&quot;numeric&quot;</span>
y <span class="o">&lt;-</span> as.character<span class="p">(</span>x<span class="p">)</span>
  <span class="p">[</span><span class="m">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="s">&quot;character&quot;</span>
class<span class="p">(</span>y<span class="p">)</span>
y
  <span class="p">[</span><span class="m">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="s">&quot;1&quot;</span> <span class="s">&quot;2&quot;</span> <span class="s">&quot;3&quot;</span>
</code></pre></div></figure>


<h3>Funkcje zwracające wektor</h3>

<p>Na przykład:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><pre><code class='r'>z12 <span class="o">&lt;-</span> <span class="kr">function</span><span class="p">(</span>z<span class="p">)</span> <span class="kr">return</span><span class="p">(</span>c<span class="p">(</span>z<span class="p">,</span> z<span class="o">^</span><span class="m">2</span><span class="p">))</span>
x <span class="o">=</span> <span class="m">1</span>:<span class="m">4</span>
matrix<span class="p">(</span>z12<span class="p">(</span>x<span class="p">),</span> ncol<span class="o">=</span><span class="m">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
     <span class="p">[,</span><span class="m">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="p">[,</span><span class="m">2</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="p">[</span><span class="m">1</span><span class="p">,]</span>    <span class="m">1</span>    <span class="m">1</span>
<span class="p">[</span><span class="m">2</span><span class="p">,]</span>    <span class="m">2</span>    <span class="m">4</span>
<span class="p">[</span><span class="m">3</span><span class="p">,]</span>    <span class="m">3</span>    <span class="m">9</span>
<span class="p">[</span><span class="m">4</span><span class="p">,]</span>    <span class="m">4</span>   <span class="m">16</span>

z12<span class="p">(</span>x<span class="p">)</span>

<span class="p">[</span><span class="m">1</span><span class="p">]</span>  <span class="m">1</span>  <span class="m">2</span>  <span class="m">3</span>  <span class="m">4</span>  <span class="m">1</span>  <span class="m">4</span>  <span class="m">9</span> <span class="m">16</span>
</code></pre></div></figure>


<h2>Praca w trybie wsadowym</h2>

<p>W pliku <em>rnorm_hist.r</em> wpisano następujące instrukcje:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span>rnorm_hist.r</span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><pre><code class='r'>pdf<span class="p">(</span><span class="s">&quot;histogram.pdf&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>
hist<span class="p">(</span>rnorm<span class="p">(</span><span class="m">1024</span><span class="p">)</span>
graphics.off<span class="p">()</span>
</code></pre></div></figure>


<p>Praca w trybie wsadowym:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><pre><code class='sh'>R --vanilla rnorm_hist.r
</code></pre></div></figure>

]]></content>
