  <entry>
    <title type="html"><![CDATA[MathJax]]></title>
    <link href="http://wbzyl.github.com/ppn/blog/2012/02/02/dodajemy-mathjax/"/>
    <updated>2012-02-02T23:45:00+01:00</updated>
    <id>http://wbzyl.github.com/ppn/blog/2012/02/02/dodajemy-mathjax</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>1. Dopisujemy do <em>source/_includes/custom/head.html</em>:</p>

<pre><code>&lt;script type="text/x-mathjax-config"&gt;
MathJax.Hub.Config({
  extensions: ["jsMath2jax.js"],
  tex2jax: {
    inlineMath: [ ['$', '$'], ['\\(', '\\)'] ],
    displayMath: [ ['$$', '$$'], ["\\[", "\\]"] ],
    processEscapes: true
  },

  "HTML-CSS": { scale: 105 },

  displayAlign: "left",
  displayIndent: "2em",

  styles: {
    ".MathJax_Display": { "color": "#A00" },
    ".MathJax": { "color": "#A00" }
  }
});
&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script src="http://cdn.mathjax.org/mathjax/latest/MathJax.js?config=TeX-AMS_HTML"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
</code></pre>

<p>Zobacz też <a href="http://www.mathjax.org/docs/1.1/options/index.html">Configuration Objects</a>.</p>

<p>2. Wzory wystawione wpisujemy tak:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><pre><code class='html'><span class="nt">&lt;div</span> <span class="na">class=</span><span class="s">math</span><span class="nt">&gt;</span>
\int\! f(x)\,dx \lt \infty
<span class="nt">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></figure>


<p>Oto rezultat:</p>

<div class=math>
\int\! f(x)\,dx \lt \infty
</div>


<p>3. Wzory w akapicie wpisujemy tak:</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span></span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><pre><code class='html'>Euler formula: $e^{i\pi} + 1 = 0$.
</code></pre></div></figure>


<p>Oto rezultat:</p>

<p>Euler formula: $e^{i\pi} + 1 = 0$.</p>


<p>4. Nie każde polecenia LaTeX-a jest poprawnie renderowane przez MathJax.
 Lista poleceń poprawnie interpretowanych jest tutaj:
<a href="http://www.mathjax.org/docs/1.1/tex.html#supported-latex-commands">Supported LaTeX commands</a>.</p>

<h2>Web Equation</h2>

<p>Co to jest? Wchodzimy na stronę
<a href="http://webdemo.visionobjects.com/equation.html?locale=default">Web Equation</a>
i wszystko jasne!</p>

<p>Więcej wzorów jest na portalu <a href="http://www.mathjax.org/">MathJax</a>
w dziale <a href="http://www.mathjax.org/demos/tex-samples/">TeX Samples</a>.</p>
]]></content>
